OL,3,CWhy the UK's sunrises and sunsets have
OL,4,Clooked so spectacular this week
OL,6,FWhy does wildfire smoke make sunrises
OL,7,Fand sunsets look more colourful?
OL,9,FWhen the sun is low in the sky, its
OL,10,Flight has to travel through much more
OL,11,Fof the atmosphere than it does at
OL,12,Fmidday.
OL,14,FAlong that journey, shorter
OL,15,Fwavelengths, such as blue light, are
OL,16,Fscattered away first, leaving the reds
OL,17,Fand oranges - making them more
OL,18,Fprominent.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
