CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1784751304
OL,3,CWhy the UK's sunrises and sunsets have
OL,4,Clooked so spectacular this week
OL,6,FThe old saying "red sky at night,
OL,7,Fshepherd's delight, red sky in the
OL,8,Fmorning, shepherd's warning" has some
OL,9,Fmeteorological truth behind it.
OL,11,FIn the UK, our weather often moves
OL,12,Ffrom west to east, so a red sunset can
OL,13,Foccur when the sun is shining through
OL,14,Fclearer air to the west, if rain-
OL,15,Fbearing clouds have moved away.
OL,17,FHowever, when wildfire smoke is
OL,18,Fpresent high in the atmosphere, it can
OL,19,Fintensify the colours regardless of
OL,20,Fwhether a weather front is approaching.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
